mayb this is like Too Much Info but whatever ive talked about having TN for so long to me it makes sense to share surgery info too. procedure went great. it was on the 22nd. i went home on the 24th.

the neurosurgeon found i had one vessel that looped around and made contact with my trigeminal nerve twice, so in two places they placed teflon between the nerve and vessel. during one of the placements, my nerve ended up pressed against the vessel, hence the current numbness

and some sensations of pressure in that same eye, likely as a result of the vice/clamp used during surgery. the left half of my tongue, around the left half of my lower lip, and my teeth on the left side of my mouth are all still numb

now that im like looking @ computer screens more, this is what went down : i had microvascular decompression surgery for trigeminal neuralgia on the 22nd. as of now we r considering it successful, as my face doesnt hurt. im dealing w/ some double vision in one eye -
around my lip is still numb and so is half of my tongue but at least it doesn't hurt anymore ?
